Introduction
“The Strip Club Chicken” brand was conceived in 2022, through 2022-2023 the brand was tested at various pop-up kitchens. The branding never failed to be a talking point.
Unfortunately due to losing my father to heart failure and a subsequent diagnosis of the same hereditary heart condition i stopped tje pop ups.
Fast forward to 2025 the menu has grown and been refined and we have rebranded ready to launch.&nbsp;
we have been let down by 3 kitchens to date. But we have now found a permanent home in a local pub garden in which we can develop the brand further, providing quality food the regulars like to eat. Driving repeat business and helping to increase wet sales for the venue. We will also focus on our social media platforms to increase brand awareness and target the delivery market. 
Why Choose “The Strip Club”
Chicken has continued to be a consistent demand, if anything it is still increasing in popularity. It is versatile, it has a broad customer appeal and is one of the more sustainable forms of meat derived protein. With quality ingredients, passionate chefs and the right branding “The Strip Club” offers a unique customer experience that will drive repeat business and help the brand organically grow through word of mouth. The addition of smash burgers and a good selection of sides ensure there is something for all tastes. 
“The Strip Club” is not a chicken shop. It is a brand. A brand we are looking to grow organically with the view to opening further branches run by trusted staff trained in our original and flagship kitchen. With the ultimate goal being franchises. &nbsp;In addition, we will also be donating some of our profits to helping local families and causes that need support through our Fund The Flock initiative. &nbsp; 
Unfortunately, &nbsp;due &nbsp;to being let down by previous kitchens we had not budgeted for a self contained container kitchen. So we need to find £6000 in order to purchase one. We have sourced a suitable kitchen. We just need to raise the finances. &nbsp;
